added.description: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
added.description: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Candy Streets
added.description: LSP is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

added.title: Blade of Grass
added.description: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man, but the sword turns out to be cursed! And unfortunately for our hero, all sales are final.

added.title: Beyond This Earthly Realm
added.description: When Finn finds a porcelain lamb, it transports him into the spirit world - and only the Ice King can help get him out!

added.title: Card Wars
added.description: Finn & Jake embark on an epic game of Card Quest.

added.title: Another Way
added.description: The tears of a crying Cyclops just might heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

added.title: Blood Under the Skin
added.description: Finn goes on an embarrassing quest to get armor to fit in with some really cool knights.

added.title: Secret Science Part 1
added.description: While studying the scraplets Wheeljack is kidnapped by Shockwave who tries to enlist Wheeljack's help.

added.title: Secret Science Part 2
added.description: Wheeljack attempts to break out of the Nemesis while Windblade hunts down Bludgeon to avenge Slipstream.

added.title: Infinite Vendetta Part 1
added.description: The Autobots and Decepticons are surprised by the return of their long-lost comrades, Jetfire and Skybyte.

added.title: Infinite Vendetta Part 2
added.description: Starscream gives Jetfire and Skybyte Spark Armor to escalate their feud and distract everyone from his machinations.

added.title: I Am the Allspark Part 1
added.description: Starscream successfully merges with the Allspark, spelling doom for the Autobots and Decepticons.

added.title: I Am the Allspark Part 2
added.description: Optimus seemingly sacrifices himself to get the Allspark back from Starscream, leaving the rest of the Autobots to deal with Megatron.

added.title: Operation: Hear No Evil
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to avoid spoilers of their favorite TV show.

added.title: Alpha Dome
added.description: The guys confront some people.

added.title: The Key to the Universe
added.description: The guys learn something super important.

added.title: Meet the Seer
added.description: The guys need to talk to someone smart.

added.title: A Regular Epic Final Battle Part 1
added.description: An epic final battle begins.

added.title: A Regular Epic Final Battle Part 2
added.description: An epic final battle comes to its dramatic conclusion, and the fate of the universe is decided.

added.title: The Button
added.description: The guys have to protect a large red button from being pushed.

added.title: Marvolo the Wizard
added.description: Pops thinks that he's a wizard trapped in medieval times, and he wants to go back home.

added.title: Pam I Am
added.description: Benson has a crush on one of the Dome scientists, and he wants to sneak her a bucket of chicken wings so that he can ask her out.

added.title: VIP Members Only
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to be VIP members at Cheeser's.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System—the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Fight at the Museum
added.description: Alien artifacts in Bellwood attract enemies from the future and friends from the past.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: The Color of Monkey
added.description: Everybody's favorite alien conman, Argit, takes on a shady sidekick, Simian, in a shocking new business.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
added.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 2
added.description: Ben and Dr. Psychobos become reluctant allies in a parallel-dimension maelstrom.

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: Third Time's a Charm
added.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: Captain Bamboozle
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk decides to create some mischief by endowing Shazam's well-meaning Uncle Dudley with superpowers bigger than anyone in the league.

added.title: El Elegido
added.description: Tobías intenta ser el mejor amigo de Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: Pijamada sin Dormir
added.description: Hay una fiesta de pijamas en el castillo, y Unikitty y Perricornio quieren quedarse despiertos toda la noche, porque creen que algo mágico debe suceder si te quedas despierto el tiempo suficiente. Al principio, los amigos están dispuestos a quedarse despiertos toda la noche. Pero cuando comienzan a quedarse dormidos de a uno, ia Unikitty le preocupa que no lo logren! ¿Hasta dónde llegarán ella y su hermano para mantenerse despiertos, y descubrirán la razón secreta por la que se supone que la gente debe irse a la cama cuando aparece El Arenero?

added.title: Sensei Halcondrilo
added.description: En una misión de rutina, Halcondrilo encuentra algunas ardillas indefensas que lo siguen como abrojos. El ave guardaespaldas decide convertirse en Sensei para enseñar a los jóvenes sus destrezas de guerrero. Pero Unikitty teme que su entrenamiento sea demasiado intenso. ¿El estilo de vida de Halcondrilo en el que todo es trabajo y no hay tiempo para el juego hará que las ardillitas sobrepasen sus límites?

added.title: Quien se llevo a Pan
added.description: Cuando Pan desaparece de la fiesta de Unikitty, ila princesa lidera una búsqueda para encontrarlo y desenmascarar al secuestrador de tostadas!

added.title: Doce Erizos Furiosas
added.description: Erizo quiere ganar la Insignia Dorada de Ciencia, pero encuentra un adversario inesperado.

added.title: Plaza Abandonada
added.description: Es el cumpleaños de KO, y Rad y Enid quieren asegurarse de que todo salga a la perfección.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La Gran Convencion de las Invenciones Elficas
added.description: Oscar, Max y Erizo le hacen un favor a la elfa Barb, a cambio de unas papas fritas.

added.title: Estan listos para el Mega Futbol?
added.description: El equipo Megafútbol de Lakewood se enfrenta a su rival en un partido importante.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Trato de Media Noche
added.description: Ramona invita a Erizo y Oscar a participar en un especial ritual celebratorio.

added.title: Nexo Creativo
added.description: Cuando KO queda atrapado dentro de un lugar misterioso, se encuentra con otros héroes de Cartoon Network y todos se unen para escapar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La Biblioteca
added.description: Los campistas pasan un día lluvioso en la biblioteca.

added.title: El Rompe Hechizos
added.description: Erizo intenta superar su enamoramiento para recuperar su enfoque en la magia.

added.title: Juego tenebroso
added.description: Últimamente, la noche semanal de juegos de mesa de la banda se volvió demasiado competitiva, así que cuando Unikitty encuentra un viejo y espeluznante juego de mesa que claramente está embrujado, los deseos de ganar del grupo quedan dados vuelta, pero con o sin embrujo, iquieren ser los primeros en cruzar la línea de llegada!

added.title: El Relopulpo
added.description: En una pacífica ciudad costera, Ben no solo debe enfrentarse a Vapor Smythe -su arcaico antagonista- y a su última creación, el Relopulpo... isino que también debe enfrentarse a su temor más profundo y oscuro: los calamares!

added.title: El vagon inacabado
added.description: El grupo entra a un vagón sin terminar e intenta arreglarlo.

added.title: Toma 10
added.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

added.title: Cambio De Edad
added.description: Durante una parada en la megatienda Shoppë, Nanny Nightmare -una niñera que se volvió loca- transforma a Ben y Gwen en bebés. Y nada la detendrá en su intento de reorganizar el mundo a imagen y semejanza de su guardería.

added.title: El vagon cromado
added.description: El grupo se encuentra con una cara familiar en un vagón espejado.

added.title: El vagon de la piscina de pelotas
added.description: El grupo es confrontado por una nueva y extraña fuerza en una aventura por un vagón lleno de pelotas.

added.title: El vagon del pasado
added.description: Tulip se arriesga al confiar en un viejo enemigo.

added.title: Impotente
added.description: El ninja corre al Museo de Historia de NINJAGO para recuperar un pergamino peligroso antes de que caiga en manos de la Hechicera Serpentina Aspheera.

added.title: La locomotora
added.description: Tulip logra llegar al frente del tren y debe afrontar una decisión.

added.title: Historia Antigua
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Principito perricornio
added.description: Puppycorn por fin se da cuenta de que es un príncipe, iy quiere estar a cargo del reino por una vez! A pesar de las preocupaciones de sus amigos, Unikitty permite que Puppycorn sea el rey, pero pronto, el poder absoluto en las manos del cachorro se le hace difícil de manejar, y sus ideas no son lo que se diría muy geniales. ¿Podrán removerlo del poder mientras evitan un levantamiento del pueblo?

added.title: Mascara de poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: Una verdad a medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Huyendo de casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un verdadero lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Pesadilla de verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Deje de Atacar el Plaza
added.description: Box-man debe pasar 24 horas sin atacar Lakewood Plaza Turbo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: No Mas Tarjetas de Poder
added.description: Cuando K.O. se da cuenta de que las Tarjetas de Poder excluyen a su amigo, no sabe qué hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Te Quiero Mao Mao
added.description: Un solitario explosivo y su mejor amigo holgazán se desvían del viaje que los llevará a convertirse en leyenda y descubren que su historia apenas comienza.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: High Dive
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps Samir overcome his paralyzing fear of the high dive.

added.title: Tiny Miracle's Tiny Miracle
added.description: Upon seeing the gang have a fun time swimming and eating ice cream, Tiny Miracle realizes he wants to be a real boy.

added.title: Exquisite Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa has been having some truly bizarre night terrors.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa: The High School Years
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and friends go way back to when they were in high school together.

added.title: Wicked Shades
added.description: When Pizza Steve borrows Uncle Grandpa's sunglasses, he sees things in a whole new light.

added.title: Except for Cooper
added.description: A young boy must learn to eat his spinach in order to save Uncle Grandpa and the others from a rowdy gang of evil vegetables.

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: Uncle Fashion
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young boy who wants to be a fashion designer by taking him somewhere his style will be appreciated.

removed.title: Mxy's Mix-Up
removed.description: As the Justice League is trying to protect the United Nations from Grodd's gorilla army, Mr. Mxyptlk pops up from the fifth dimension and thinks it would be great fun to put each of the superheroes' brains into another hero's body.

removed.title: Booster's Gold
removed.description: Green Arrow becomes involved with Booster Gold when he discovers that the self-centered superhero has brought dinosaurs back from the past for a money-making venture.

removed.title: Nuclear Family Values
removed.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

removed.title: All Aboard the Space Train
removed.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

removed.description: Plastic Man feels shuffled off to the side as the Justice League battles Brainiac so he takes it upon himself to infiltrate the alien's ship on his own and thwart the villain's plans.

removed.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
removed.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

removed.description: Adorabat siente que es dejada de lado y desea que Mao Mao y Colosal pasen menos tiempo juntos y más tiempo con ella. Pero cuando el deseo de Adorabat se hace realidad y destruye la amistad de Mao Mao y Colosal, solo el secreto de su pasado podrá volver a unirlos.

removed.title: Dia de Spa
removed.description: Los Osos se relajan en el spa. Grizz intenta usar todos los servicios del spa. Panda queda atrapado en la sala de vapor con un anciano. Y Polar juega al ping pong.

removed.title: El Cumpleanos de Panda
removed.description: Para el cumpleaños de Panda, los Osos intentan ayudarlo a conocer a su banda favorita de K-pop, Monsta X.

removed.description: Cuando los Osos asisten a una reunión con la familia de Chloe, se convierten en víctimas de Jon, el travieso primo de Chloe.

removed.description: Gumball y Darwin intentan unirse a la pandilla de los más malos de la ciudad.

removed.description: Tras esforzarse por mantener el ritmo en las batallas, Adorabat consigue una armadura cibernética. ¿Pero podrán unos nuevos y sofisticados poderes compensar la falta de experiencia?

removed.title: Sitiados
removed.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

removed.title: La Jaula
removed.description: Los niños convencen al Sr. Corneille de que se suba a un cuadrilátero y le organizan una pelea contra un temible luchador ruso.
removed.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

removed.title: Goose Chase
removed.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

removed.title: Time Crimes
removed.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

removed.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

removed.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

removed.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

removed.description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

removed.title: Apple's Focus
removed.description: Apple helps Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

removed.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

removed.title: Duck Duck Juice
removed.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

removed.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
removed.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

removed.title: Dawn Before Dusk
removed.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

removed.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets

removed.title: The Perfect Adventure
removed.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

removed.title: No Shortcuts
removed.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?

removed.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

removed.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.
